All Classes

  • All Classes Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    Debugger
    Debugger sends messages to the console when a Locale is loaded into or cleared from the cache, by default this is disabled.
    Locale
    An enum of all locale codes used by Minecraft which defines the language of the player's client.
    LocaleCacheLoader
    LocaleCacheLoader is used for loading a specific LocaleReader with the provided Locale to the cache.
    LocaleChangeListener  
    LocaleCounter
    LocaleCounter is counting how many players are using a Locale.
    LocaleReader
    LocalReader is used for loading a Locale from the resources folder and accessing their keys and values.
    Translate
    With Translate you can translate Biomes Materials Potions PotionEffects Enchantments Entities TropicalFishes Villager with the giving Locale or Player(uses Translate.getLocale(Player))
    Translate.PotionSort
    An enum of all potion types.
    UsedLocalesCommand
